review_text:
The Delta Cottage is a nicely hidden spot not far from Indianola and the B.B. King museum, for the real Blues lovers. However, keep in mind about a number of things:
- ask Lars in advance the access code to the gate, otherwise you cannot enter the property (and it takes an hour for you to get in, as we had);
- the pool is sometimes not usable, we were there at the end of May and there was unfortunately no water in it (while we had explicitly chosen the Delta Cottage because of the pool);
- it has windows all around, not all of which can be blinded, so that means you will be up very early;
- and bring all the food and drinks (water and for your breakfast on the porch, among other things) yourself.
